---
layout: default
title: Home
nav: home
description: "Mechanistic electrochemical diagnostics for interfaces, degradation, corrosion, and transport."
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="section-kicker">Kyung Hee University · Chemical Engineering</span>
      <h1>Mechanistic Electrochemical Diagnostics</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Decoding interfaces, degradation, corrosion, and transport from electrochemical signals.</p>
      <p class="hero-description">Yoon Lab develops quantitative electrochemical diagnostics that connect measurable signals with the hidden mechanisms governing performance, lifetime, and failure in energy materials and devices.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn primary" href="{{ '/research/' | relative_url }}">Research →</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="{{ '/publications/' | relative_url }}">Publications →</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="{{ '/join/' | relative_url }}">Join Us →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="signal-card" aria-label="Abstract electrochemical signal illustration">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 420" role="img">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="wave" x1="0" x2="1">
            <stop offset="0" stop-color="#d6a21e"/>
            <stop offset="1" stop-color="#70b8ff"/>
          </linearGradient>
          <radialGradient id="node" cx="50%" cy="50%" r="50%">
            <stop offset="0" stop-color="#fff1c2"/>
            <stop offset="1" stop-color="#d6a21e"/>
          </radialGradient>
        </defs>
        <rect width="520" height="420" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.02)"/>
        <path d="M40 300 C100 210, 145 350, 210 240 S315 175, 372 238 S444 315, 488 190" fill="none" stroke="url(#wave)" stroke-width="6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <path d="M52 338 H476" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.25)"/>
        <path d="M70 348 V72" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.25)"/>
        <text x="405" y="365" fill="rgba(255,255,255,.55)" font-size="18">Z′</text>
        <text x="28" y="88" fill="rgba(255,255,255,.55)" font-size="18">−Z″</text>
        <g stroke="rgba(255,255,255,.3)" stroke-width="2">
          <line x1="260" y1="78" x2="325" y2="118"/>
          <line x1="325" y1="118" x2="392" y2="82"/>
          <line x1="325" y1="118" x2="326" y2="190"/>
          <line x1="326" y1="190" x2="392" y2="230"/>
          <line x1="326" y1="190" x2="258" y2="228"/>
        </g>
        <g>
          <circle cx="260" cy="78" r="13" fill="url(#node)"/>
          <circle cx="325" cy="118" r="18" fill="#70b8ff" opacity=".95"/>
          <circle cx="392" cy="82" r="12" fill="url(#node)"/>
          <circle cx="326" cy="190" r="18" fill="#70b8ff" opacity=".85"/>
          <circle cx="392" cy="230" r="13" fill="url(#node)"/>
          <circle cx="258" cy="228" r="12" fill="url(#node)"/>
        </g>
        <text x="82" y="84" fill="rgba(255,255,255,.62)" font-size="20">EIS · DRT · PITT · QCM</text>
        <text x="282" y="314" fill="rgba(255,255,255,.45)" font-size="18">interface / transport / side reaction</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-panel">
      <span class="section-kicker">From signals to mechanisms</span>
      <p>Our research connects electrochemical measurements with real interfacial phenomena in batteries, solid-state and polymer electrolytes, corrosion systems, supercapacitors, seawater electrolysis, and electrochemical sensors. We focus on translating signals such as impedance, transient current, and mass change into mechanistic understanding of degradation and failure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-kicker">Research Themes</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Quantitative Diagnostics for Electrochemical Systems</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">We use electrochemical signals as quantitative probes of hidden interfacial states, transport processes, side reactions, corrosion, and degradation across energy materials and devices.</p>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 34px;">
      {% for theme in site.data.research %}
      <article class="theme-card">
        <div class="theme-icon">{% include icon.html name=theme.icon %}</div>
        <div>
          <h3>{{ theme.title }}</h3>
          <p>{{ theme.description }}</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container split">
    <div>
      <span class="section-kicker">Selected Research Highlights</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Representative achievements</h2>
      <div class="highlight-list">
        {% for item in site.data.highlights %}
        <article class="highlight-card">
          <div class="highlight-year">{{ item.year }}</div>
          <div class="highlight-body">
            <small>{{ item.tag }}</small>
            <h3>{{ item.journal }}</h3>
            <p>{{ item.title }}</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside>
      <span class="section-kicker">News & Opportunities</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Latest from the lab</h2>
      {% assign latest_news = site.data.news | sort: "date" | reverse %}
{% for item in latest_news limit:3 %}
     <article class="news-card">
  <span class="category">{{ item.category }}</span>
  <h3>{{ item.title }}</h3>
  <p>{{ item.summary }}</p>
  <time datetime="{{ item.date }}">{{ item.display_date | default: item.date }}</time>
</article>
{% endfor %}
      <a class="btn secondary" href="{{ '/news/' | relative_url }}" style="margin-top: 10px; color: var(--navy-900); border-color: rgba(201,154,46,.45); background: var(--white);">All news →</a>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="callout">
      <div>
        <h2>Join Yoon Lab</h2>
        <p>We welcome motivated students interested in batteries, electrochemical diagnostics, corrosion, safety, solid-state and polymer electrolytes, and quantitative analysis of interfacial reactions.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn primary" href="{{ '/join/' | relative_url }}">Open positions →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
